<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Standing-Dumbbell-3-Way-Shoulder-Raise">Standing Dumbbell 3-Way Shoulder Raise</h3>



<p>This shoulder exercise is one that really gets those muscles burning. You may need to avoid heavy weights to thwart shoulder injuries and opt for a lighter weight for this one. Check out the steps below to learn how to do it.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides with palms facing your thighs. Make sure to have a slight bend in your elbows.</li>



<li>Lift both dumbbells in front of you until your arms are parallel to the ground.</li>



<li>Then, move both arms outward, keeping them parallel to the ground.</li>



<li>Lastly, lower the dumbbells back to the starting position and repeat.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Make sure to keep a slight bend in your elbows the entire time.</li>



<li>Choose a lighter weight that allows you to finish the entire sequence to enhance your range of motion. It&#8217;s better to focus on muscle engagement rather than heavy lifting for this exercise.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



